1
00:00:03,360 --> 00:00:04,240
Dude, this is cool.

2
00:00:04,320 --> 00:00:05,920
You know it’s also a GPS, right?

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,640
It can save you a ton of time on the road.

4
00:00:07,720 --> 00:00:09,560
I don’t need a GPS, I can drive on my own.

5
00:00:09,640 --> 00:00:11,760
And leave me the phone alone, do me a favor.
-Okay, come on, babe,

6
00:00:11,840 --> 00:00:13,760
I just want to see if it’s a guy’s
or a girl’s voice saying,

7
00:00:13,840 --> 00:00:17,240
"Turn right," "Turn right."

8
00:00:17,320 --> 00:00:19,720
Sit down, do me a favor, leave it alone,
it’s new. You’ll mess it up.

9
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:21,720
Fine, I won’t mess it up, relax.

10
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:23,120
I have the instructions here, I’m doing what it says.

11
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:24,680
But it’s not about what’s written.

12
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:27,440
You wash the washing machine
exactly like it says, right?

13
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:28,960
The technician said it happens to everyone.

14
00:00:29,560 --> 00:00:31,760
And the streamer?
-I’m not to blame it doesn’t say "delete" on it

15
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:33,320
like all the normal devices.

16
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:34,400
And the alarm clock?

17
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:36,360
Just because your mom gets mad when we’re late, it’s not my fault.

18
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:38,840
Want me to tell you what all these instructions are for?

19
00:00:39,720 --> 00:00:43,680
So there’s work for all those technicians
who come to your house

20
00:00:43,760 --> 00:00:46,800
and act like they don’t understand
how you didn’t fix it yourself.

21
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:49,480
Huh?
-What did you do? What did you touch?

22
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:52,560
Chill out, God. What’s wrong with you?

23
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:55,200
I updated it a bit, it’s just that...

24
00:00:55,720 --> 00:00:57,760
It switched to Norwegian.
-What?

25
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,800
No, everything’s fine, come on,
I’ll fix it in a second.

26
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:02,160
It’s just Norwegian.
-What?

27
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:05,440
Norwegian, Norwegian, okay?
It switched to Norwegian. What do you want?

28
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,280
Chill out, I’ll sort it out.

29
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:11,880
Tell me, does "valg" mean "choose" or "delete"?

30
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:19,760
Look at me, look at me and...

31
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:32,160
Shabbat Shalom.
-Happy holiday.

32
00:01:32,240 --> 00:01:34,960
Happy holiday, the boys are already coming.

33
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:38,360
What holiday and what happy? Why did you have to touch it?

34
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:40,240
Enough, babe, I said I’m sorry.

35
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:42,320
So what? You said sorry,
does that cancel everything?

36
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:45,200
In the spirit of the holiday?
-It’s not a holiday in Norway right now.

37
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:47,560
Okay, enough, enough. I have the instruction sheet here.
Give it to me,

38
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:51,640
I’ll fix it for you in a second.
-You’re not touching that! You messed it up and now you’re inheriting it?

39
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,400
My connectivity fees are crying from the ground.
-Fine.

40
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:55,520
Don’t touch it.
-Okay, fine, come on, you’re just being cranky,

41
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:58,080
I get you and it’s not from that,
it’s from all these holidays

42
00:01:58,160 --> 00:02:01,520
where every other day is Friday and the boys are always
with their families at all kinds of meals.

43
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:04,040
It’s family "overdose,"
who wouldn’t get annoyed by that?

44
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:07,040
I’m not annoyed by that, I’m annoyed that
you messed up my phone.

45
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:10,400
She’s annoying him again.
-I can relate.

46
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:12,320
Does she annoy you too, Shani?

47
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:14,720
Did she forget where to put the socks?

48
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:16,160
No.
-Then no.

49
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:18,120
Pinchas, why are you blaming me?

50
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:23,520
I clearly remember you put it
in the decoration box after the holiday.

51
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:24,800
I’m telling you I didn’t.

52
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:27,680
You put it there!
-You did!

53
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,440
You don’t have to be so cranky.

54
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:33,320
Just so you know, you don’t find things when you’re angry.

55
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:39,000
Enough, you don’t fix things when you’re angry.

56
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:42,000
Hello, happy holiday.
-Happy holiday, Riki.

57
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,680
Happy holiday.
-Happy holiday.

58
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:49,280
It’s been a while since we saw each other.
-Two days.

59
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:52,320
Mom, what’s the deal with the leftovers?
-On Sukkot evening?

60
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:55,440
No, I thought maybe
he survived the break-fast meal.

61
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:58,000
Yeah, I don't know who made those meals.

62
00:02:58,080 --> 00:03:01,560
Shai, go set up the sukkah,
Dad took it down from the attic.

63
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:04,600
Well, let me fix your phone in the meantime.
-Don't touch it.

64
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:07,560
I'll sort it out quickly
and fix the phone without instructions.

65
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:12,160
"We'll grab iron rods fast

66
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:15,760
to build a sukkah in five minutes..."

67
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,400
So what...

68
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,520
What's new?

69
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:32,160
Since Saturday?

70
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:36,760
Do you need me to help you in the kitchen?
-Yeah.

71
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,560
No, it's not here either.

72
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,040
What is it? What happened?

73
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:46,320
Riki can't remember where she put the garlic press.

74
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:47,880
It's the same thing every year.

75
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:51,000
I clearly remember Pinchas packed it up

76
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:52,520
last year.
-You.

77
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:55,880
Okay, fine. Even if you don't find it,
it's not a big deal, I'll make decorations with the girls.

78
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,880
And the mess?
-No glue.

79
00:03:57,960 --> 00:04:00,760
Just scissors, a stapler, and old magazines
-Okay.

80
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:02,480
On the balcony.

81
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:05,200
You don't have to be so stubborn.

82
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:08,080
We have a garlic press, we're using the garlic press.

83
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:10,920
Why are we keeping all this stuff?

84
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,840
When was the last time we used this?

85
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,000
What even is this?

86
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,120
I, I remember,

87
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:20,920
it's a gift Itamar gave you for your 56th birthday.

88
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,320
Yeah, but what is it?
-A device, how should I know.

89
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,960
It's a nose hair trimmer.
-Oh.

90
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:32,440
In the hallway. That's exactly what I wanted to talk to you about.

91
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:38,080
Here it said "choose," "and go,"

92
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:40,080
so later it's in the back...

93
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:44,320
Right?
-Well, what's up? Did you come to look for the instructions?

94
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:47,320
No, I forgot the sugar.
-Okay, you won't believe what's happening in the kitchen.

95
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,560
If it's not schnitzel, I'm not interested.

96
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:49,880
I'll tell you three things.

97
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:54,160
Your mom, your dad, and a nose hair trimmer.
-Got it.

98
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,840
Looking for the garlic press?
-Yeah.

99
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,480
And if it's in your dad's nose,

100
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,000
there's a chance they'll find it too.

101
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:00,800
Oh, my mom can be so stubborn.

102
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:03,240
Right, lucky she didn't pass that down to you.

103
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:05,240
Just bring the phone already!
-No.

104
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:07,000
But I know how to fix it,
I saw in the instructions.

105
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:09,680
Not giving it to you. Go find something else to mess with.

106
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:12,240
Okay, fine, then I'll go
make decorations with the girls for the sukkah.

107
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:15,800
Make sure there are instructions.
-Funny.

108
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:18,400
Very funny, I'm cracking up.

109
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:21,920
Hello, happy holiday.
-Happy holiday.

110
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:24,040
How's it going?

111
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:27,040
Heh
Heh

112
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:29,480
What’s this, we didn’t see each other two days ago?
-Because,

113
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:30,880
I'm just happy, that's all.

114
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:34,360
What's with the magazines?
-Decorations for the sukkah.

115
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:36,720
Oh, how nice, so do you want to...

116
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,680
Yeah, honey, maybe you should go with Shani
to really make decorations for the sukkah,

117
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,800
in the meantime, I'll grab some schnitzels, something.

118
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:43,640
Sukkot, no schnitzels. I've been through this.

119
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:46,000
I totally forgot, the days got mixed up for me.

120
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,760
So honey, do you want to make the decorations together
for...

121
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:51,440
Babe, I need to go with Shai to build the sukkah.

122
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:52,800
Just like when we were kids.

123
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:55,080
Remember how we used to build the sukkah together?
-Of course.

124
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:56,600
You held the nails.

125
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,800
I hammered them in!
-For sure.

126
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:00,800
So now it’s a sukkah for life, much safer.

127
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,600
Definitely.
-Let’s go.

128
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,520
Oh, decorations.
-Decorations.

129
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:07,200
Is it over there?
-No.

130
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:12,720
Pinchas, I think you need to
prepare for the worst:

131
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:17,680
There’s a chance we won’t find the garland.
-It’s Sukkot,

132
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:20,400
and the garland is part of the Sukkot tradition,

133
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:23,640
I’ll find the garland
even if I have to search until Hanukkah.

134
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:27,280
And if I find the sun, I’ll put
it aside so you don’t pack it too.

135
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:29,800
You don’t have to be so grumpy.

136
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:34,200
Besides, it’s kind of nice to find some of the stuff here.
-Thanks.

137
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:36,600
We already found the thorn! Nice is not it.

138
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:39,560
Oh, look, there are pictures
of the kids when they were little.

139
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:41,280
Wow.

140
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,800
Itamar!

141
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:44,160
And Adam,

142
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,400
such cuties.

143
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:50,440
Hey! What a cute family back then.

144
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:54,840
What happened that it all fell apart?
-Do you need help, Riki?

145
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:59,000
No, you’ve helped enough already.

146
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:03,920
I don’t need instructions, it’s a sukkah for life,
what do we need instructions for?

147
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,960
For inspiration, okay?
-Fine, okay.

148
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:07,560
Come on, quick, while Michal is there.

149
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:12,000
Wait, tell me,
what’s with this sudden isolation vibe?

150
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:16,520
The kids went with Smadar to the Maldives,
Michal finished studying and has time

151
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,400
and she decided to spend that time with me.

152
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:21,120
And that’s not good?

153
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:24,880
I volunteered to build a sukkah with them, right?

154
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,960
Uh-huh.
-Uh-huh.

155
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,400
Ugh, I thought we were in decoration mode.

156
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,880
It’s okay, don’t worry, they’ll soon give up searching.

157
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:35,720
Gross.

158
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:38,400
So what? You’re without kids now, huh?

159
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,760
Sounds fun.
-I wish I could live like this forever,

160
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:44,120
I’m telling you, I’m just happy.

161
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,000
Really?
-Yeah.

162
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:49,880
Look, honestly, after Itamar
supported me so nicely in my studies

163
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:51,920
and was such a considerate husband, giving me time alone

164
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,160
and living with the fact that his wife is a student,

165
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:57,160
he deserves to just
accept me 100%, right?

166
00:07:57,720 --> 00:08:00,920
Yeah. I hope he knows how to appreciate that.
-Of course.

167
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:04,480
It’s not just the restaurants! The museums and clubs,

168
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:07,000
I mean, it’s the most fun, don’t get me wrong,

169
00:08:07,080 --> 00:08:09,480
but the main thing is just the time I have! with Itamar,

170
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:13,600
24/7, I call it "Itamar time."

171
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:18,040
She calls it "Itamar time."
-Wow, you’re really into it.

172
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:20,480
And it’s not that she drags me
to all the museums, restaurants, clubs,

173
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:22,440
I suffer from it, don’t get me wrong,

174
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:24,560
it’s that I have to do it with her 24/7.

175
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:26,920
Tough, tough.
-And why do I deserve this?

176
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:29,360
No, Shai, why do I deserve this?
What, I was a model husband,

177
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,800
I gave her time to study,
time for herself, to be a student.

178
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:33,880
I was happy to come here, Shai.

179
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:36,080
I miss my kids, you know.

180
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:38,440
Take comfort in the fact that you can call them.

181
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,760
At least she didn't break your phone.

182
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:42,679
What, Shani read the instructions
and thought she understood them?

183
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,440
Oh come on
just come and

184
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,080
I'll sort it out for you without instructions or anything.

185
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,320
You know what the problem is
with today's technology?

186
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:51,520
Everything's too accessible, too available.

187
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,320
Back in the day, if you needed something,
you needed a toolbox,

188
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,600
you needed a screwdriver, you needed a Phillips,
you needed a hammer.

189
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:57,120
Today, you just have to touch it.

190
00:08:57,680 --> 00:08:59,920
So what you're saying
is that if a screwdriver was involved,

191
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,720
then Shani wouldn't have broken my phone at all?

192
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:03,400
No, Shani would have broken it anyway.

193
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:08,160
I have no technical knowledge.
Who put up the shelf in the living room?

194
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,480
Oh, the one that's a bit slanted?

195
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:12,320
It's not crooked, it's designed. Don't be a smartass now.

196
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:14,480
So, what's the size of their storage?

197
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:17,520
Do they really need that clutter?
I thought we could do some decorations.

198
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,080
Come on, you want to mess with the Rosen family?

199
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:21,160
Will this get me out of doing Passover here?

200
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:23,120
Only death frees you from obligations, not Passover.

201
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:26,120
Energy generation
I.B.
create
B.K.
okay, A

202
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:29,160
I'm going to make chains on the balcony.
-Alright, I'm coming with you.

203
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:32,560
I think I managed to connect to help,

204
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,600
Jay is a...

205
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:37,440
Hoolap, hoolap...

206
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:38,680
And now what?

207
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,720
Do you understand Norwegian?

208
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:50,600
Who is it?
-Shai, it's Adam.

209
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:51,520
Your brother is here.

210
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,120
Great.
-Are you coming up?

211
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:56,000
Wait, wait, tell me, are those metal rods down there
our sukkah?

212
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,920
Yeah, but they're coming down, looking for the instructions.

213
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,560
What instructions? It's a sukkah.
-I'm on my way.

214
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:02,760
Who was that?
-Adam.

215
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:06,200
How are you guys? It's really late.
-It's fine, it's ready.

216
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:09,720
There aren't many boxes left.
Didn't I tell you it's not there?

217
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:11,520
I'm here with the food.

218
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:15,680
Grandma, what do we eat for Sukkot?

219
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:18,920
For Sukkot, we eat festive food,

220
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:22,720
but it has a secret spice.

221
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:26,480
Do you want to guess what the secret spice is?

222
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:27,600
Turmeric?
-Cumin?

223
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:30,520
No. Who raised you, girls?

224
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,400
The secret spice:

225
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,800
Sugar.
-Sugar?

226
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:37,560
Boy, what?
ﭏ נניּרע
אונ')

227
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:43,920
Does Mom know? Go, go, go to Mom,
go help her a bit with the decorations.

228
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,600
Where are the phone instructions?

229
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:50,000
That's it, Shani took the instructions
because I told her I could do without.

230
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:55,920
What?

231
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,640
Come on, what's going on?
-Good, come down and help him.

232
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:58,760
We're coming, we're coming.

233
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,600
Oh, is this it?

234
